# Ruby / Rails / Chatwoot

- Follow Rails and project conventions; prefer the layer the repo already uses (model, service, job, controller).
- Keep validations, callbacks, and associations intentional; prefer clear service boundaries over callback-heavy hidden behavior.
- Use background jobs for async work the repo already treats asynchronously; keep payloads idempotent when retries matter.
- Respect Chatwoot-style boundaries for inbox, conversation, message, and automation flows unless the repo explicitly changes them.
